Definition.WordDefinition:
Genital \Gen"i*tal\, a. [L. genitalis, fr. genere, gignere, to beget: cf. F. g['e]nital. See {Gender}.] Pertaining to generation, or to the generative organs; as, genital herpes. [1913 Webster]
{Genital cord} (Anat.), a cord developed in the fetus by the union of portions of the Wolffian and M["u]llerian ducts and giving rise to parts of the urogenital passages in both sexes. [1913 Webster]
